name: Dave Marrs
bio:
Dad | Husband to @jennymarrs | Builder | Craftsman  
Fixer to Fabulous @hgtv | #fixertofab

social_posts.post_text: Remembering a fun commercial Jenny and I shot for @daikincomfort which you can check out during the rebroadcast of Fixer to Fabulous tomorrow. It’s great shooting commercials of products you already use and love, and it means the world to Jenny and I that Daikin believes in our show and requested to be in the ad space! #daikin #ad
So very excited to tell you all about @jennymarrs and my next project!! And yes, it’s in Europe because I don’t wear a scarf anywhere else.  Stay tuned!

Yes, the expression on my face and my brother Matt’s is that of complete confusion.  @jennymarrs bought concrete fire balls for the fireplace on tonight’s episode.  Have you ever seen these things?  Definitely a different take on the wood looking logs you usually see in a fireplace.  Tonight’s episode is full of surprises for such a wonderful couple who are changing our town for the better!  Hope you can watch tonight on @hgtv at 9/8 central.

Ok.  I’m not gonna lie, I get cold in the winter.  Yes, it’s cheating a little having a battery powered jacket, but I don’t care.  This new jacket from @harttoolsusa is great, and uses the same battery as my Hart power tools.  They also have blankets.  Great holiday gift idea!  Check out the link in my bio.  #ad
Winter is here!  I don’t know why it makes me happy seeing all those heads buried in the hay.  They just crack me up.  Have a wonderful day!
Wrapping up one of the final reveals for season 4 of Fixer to Fabulous!  I love watching @jennymarrs do interviews.  Simple daily reminders of how truly blessed I am to call her my partner and wife.
Hope you all catch tonight’s episode of Fixer to Fabulous at 9/8 c on @hgtv.  Luke is definitely a small version of me.
Love having my girls help with the show projects.  Tonight is another brand new great episode.  A beautiful lake house.  Hope you can watch at 9/8 c on @hgtv
The cold weather is here.  Bundle up!!!!

Man it’s cold!  So cold the tractor wouldn’t start; I know I should have prepared more😬. But, it made me realize two things: 1. Great neighbors who say “sure Dave come grab my tractor” are priceless.  2.  I now need a bigger tractor. 😂👍. @jennymarrs is not going to be happy.
Definitely in her element!  @jennymarrs and Belle.  It’s Christmas Eve.  Hope you are all celebrating with those you love!!!
Unfortunately plumbers crack is hereditary in the Marrs family.  Sorry Luke😂😂😂

Probably one of my favorite living rooms of season 4 happened last night.  The house was in great shape, it just reminded @jennymarrs and I too much of a “Wonder Years” episode shot in 1985.  Adding the natural stone and real oak beams to the kitchen made the difference.  Hope you get to check it out on @hgtv

Happy happy birthday to my beautiful Sylvie Marrs.  11 years old today.  So, I thought why not choreograph a skating dance with my her and Charlotte.  Didn’t realize I am truly terrible at roller skating.  Anyway, love you Sylvie.

See that strapping young lad in the overalls and bowl haircut.  No, it’s not a young Brad Pitt, it’s actually me building a log cabin with my dad.  I grew up in Colorado building homes with my dad and brother.  Well, on tonight’s episode of Fixer to Fabulous, @jennymarrs and I get to rehab a beautiful log home here in Northwest Arkansas.  Such a great project that brought up so many great memories of growing up!  Hope you all get to watch at 9/8c on @hgtv

This woman!  Today is @jennymarrs birthday!  I’ve got to tell you, she’s never looked better.  She’s a wonderful mother, wife, and partner in this crazy life we lead. 
  God knows the shepherd Jenny is, and gave her twins to take care of the day before we are supposed to have the biggest snow storm of the year.  He knew they would be put in wonderful, caring hands.  He also knows what is the best possible present she could receive, and gave it to her.  So, on this freezing cold day, this is where you will find Jenny truly celebrating her birthday.  It started in a robe and will end in a snowsuit, and the smile will never leave her beautiful face.  Help me to wish Jenny Marrs a blessed happy birthday!

Building homes sometimes feels like being on an island.  You aren’t in an office where you can collaborate.  But once a year, @jennymarrs and I head to the builders show.  This year we came with @cornerstone_buildingbrands and had an amazing time.  They have so many new innovative products I can’t wait to start using on the houses!  It’s just incredible to see the advances in building, especially on the exterior of the home.  Anyway, love a few wonderful days away with my beautiful wife!  Now back to freezing temperatures, farming, and 5 kids.  The builders show may need to be a week next year. 🥶😂😂

Are animals and humans really that different?
I can hear Dee, our baby sheep, now. “Don’t worry mom, I’ve got it”. 😂😂😂. Two weeks old and already crazy!  Hope you all have a wonderful weekend!

Happy birthday to this beautiful woman I get to call Mom!  She is my hero, and my friend.  I never thought she could be better than a mom, then she became a Nana.  So blessed to celebrate this day with such an incredible woman!

Ok.  You all have to watch tonight’s episode of Fixer to Fabulous!  I built a shuffle board table and it worked perfectly.  One of the most fun projects I have ever done.  Everything about tonight was fun.  Taking an old barn and making it into a home for a family was challenging and something I hope to do again.  Tune in soon to @hgtv at 9/8 central!!!!!

I have a few weeks where I need to get as much of the @jennymarrs honey-do-list done as possible. Number one was the guest bathroom that everyone uses when they come into our house. It was an old door that didn’t close, didn’t lock, and didn’t latch. So I took some 6 x 6 sassafras posts and ripped them down into smaller pieces so I could create a door that looks pretty for Jenny; Functions properly for guests; And a bonus for our kids,  smells exactly like root beer.  1 project down, 100 to go.

I know we don’t have a new episode this week but we are gearing up for next weeks new episode and next season getting fresh wood ready for projects.  We mill lumber from properties all around northwest Arkansas.  It will then sit in my open air barn for a couple years before it’s ready for projects.  I love how abundant this area is for amazing lumber
Sunday afternoons are for long walks down deserted roads with your kids
Tonight on Fixer to Fabulous we bring bring Peru to Bentonville.  Such a fun project.  Hope you can all watch at 9/8 central on @hgtv.
There are definitely worse places for a morning walk!

You might think this is another wine wall, but it’s not!  This one is all for kids.  Check out the finished product tonight on Fixer to Fabulous on @hgtv  Hope you all catch the new episode at 9/8 central.

I hope you all get to catch Episode 1 of Rock the Block tonight on @hgtv.  @jennymarrs and I judged space number 1, the Kitchen.  These four teams were incredible.  All of them had such amazing spaces.  So hard just picking one winner.  It was good to be back on the block and see some old friends and meet some new.  Best of luck teams!

Today’s the day! A new episode of #fixertofab airs tonight at 9|8c on @hgtv. Dave made an incredible pirate ship that has got to be one of our favorite projects. We love getting to design kid’s spaces, especially fun ones like this. Tune in tonight to check out more of the home!

Do you ever look at your life and have one of those moments?  Moments where you are so thankful for the life God has blessed you with?  The simple act of making dinner with Charlotte and Luke did that for me today.  Sometimes the most ordinary task becomes extraordinary!

Nothing like fresh semolina pasta on a rainy Saturday with my girl.  It’s super easy and fun.  Ingredients:  8 cups organic semolina flour.  2-3 cups of hot water.  6 tablespoons olive oil.  1 tablespoon sea salt.  Combine ingredients, add water a little at a time until you have a springy dough ball.  Knead for 5 minutes then wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate to rest for minimum of 30 minutes.  After that roll out dry and enjoy.  Mine only has to boil for about 3 minutes.  Next up, my brother in laws homemade sauce recipe.

Going way back into the archives for this one. I posted this photo on July 21, 2022. At the time, we knew we wanted to do something amazing with this historic building on our little town’s Main Street. We have dreamt of a way for this building to kick off the revitalization of this street and, while it took some time, we finally restored her and created something that we are really, really proud of. 

In tonight’s all-new episode of Fixer to Fabulous, watch us transform the second floor of the building!! This one is so big that we are sharing as a two-part restoration…we’re saving the big finale for next week 😉. (Swipe for a peek inside of the before!)

This one is personal for us and I’m nervous and excited and honored to share it with you all! See you tonight at 9|8c on @hgtv !!! 🤍

#fixertofabulous

Tonight is the night! @jennymarrs and I get to celebrate the end of season four with a project that is so special to us. Our own store! The Marrs Mercantile opening April 1. This was a chance to highlight all of the things and local vendors we love. We hope you all get to come to Northwest Arkansas and check it out!  Watch tonight at 9/8c on @hgtv

Gotta remember the bathroom, it needs furniture too.  This walnut piece fits perfectly in such a cool bathroom.  From the tile, to the walls, to the safe door, you gotta come check it out.  If you can’t, be sure and watch tonight at  9/8 central on @hgtv

We had such a fun, relaxing week in Gulf Shores, Alabama.  One of our favorite activities is fishing from the ocean.  For the past several years, our good friend Troy loads up all his gear, comes to our rental, and puts my kids on fish.  It’s perfect because they can fish, eat, play in the sand, etc. without ever getting bored.  This year we added catching blue crabs to the fun.  I highly recommend it!  This is the last hurrah before we start filming season 5 of Fixer to Fabulous.  It think it’s going to be a great year.  We already have so many great homeowners, with some really amazing builds.  Look for it this fall!
The blueberries aren’t awake yet but the bees are in full force.  Time to try and get a new beehive from one of our hives splitting!!!!

Today is @jennymarrs and my Anniversary.  For 18 years we have built a home and family together here in Arkansas.  We have 5 beautiful children, way to many animals, too much work , and never enough time.  And I wouldn’t change a minute of it.  I don’t know what life still has in store for us but I’m glad I get to share it with such an incredible person.
Gotta start those beekeepers young!  I love how the kids want to help with the bees.  More suits should be arriving soon!!!

Jenny and I are excited to be using Mastic Siding by @plygem on our exterior projects. Check out our latest install of Mastic’s Structure® Home Insulation System™ siding. This high-performance vinyl is perfect for new homes and home remodeling, bringing superior insulating power that lowers bills and wraps the home in protection. See more of Mastic’s premium siding options at mastic.com. #sponsored #masticsiding #plygem
The sand plums are in full bloom!  The whole farm is blooming right now.  Can’t wait to share it all with you this summer @theberryfarm_bentonville
Charlottes never ending quest to successfully ride Daddy Donk.  I love it.  Now she’s involved friends in this task.

Can’t believe I got to meet Jenna and Reba on the today show to talk about Hometown Takeover that @jennymarrs and I filmed with @scotsman.co and @erinapier.  Don’t miss it.  The premiere is this Sunday at 8/7c on @hgtv

The stories we were given the opportunity to be a part of were the reason we said yes to joining this season of Hometown Takeover. This show is all about highlighting real people doing the real work of raising kids and managing businesses and helping their community. It’s pure, feel-good television and I know we can all use more of this in our lives. 🫶🥹

We are thrilled to join our friends, Erin and Ben Napier, (and many others! @jonathanrknight and @mollyyeh join us on tonight’s episode!) on an amazing journey to revitalize an entire town. It all begins TONIGHT (Sunday) at 8|7c #OnHGTV! 🤍
Tonight on Hometown Takeover on @hgtv you will meet some of the absolute best people.  These families are essential to a successful Fort Morgan.  Check it out at 8/7 central.

Big things happening in Italy! Can’t really talk about it yet, but do you see that camera in the background?  Has anyone ever seen a wall filled floor to ceiling with wallpaper that is 100 years old?  I love the history here!
Tonight on #HomeTownTakeover, we take on a fun bowling alley transformation and we renovate a home for an incredible family! Watch tonight at 8|7c on @hgtv🎳
Perfect weekend to celebrate Mom at the lake.  The boys and I had to get the boat out and ready for summer.  Headed to pick up the rest of the family.  That water is 🥶.

This woman!  jenny marrs living it up on a tube in freezing cold water because her daughter asked her to ride.  That’s the kind of mother she is!  Happy Mother’s Day to all of you selfless women always putting your kids first!
My beautiful little girl is 9 today!  Happy happy birthday Charlotte Marrs!  Your mom and I love you with all our hearts.
I absolutely love being in the fields on a rainy morning.
Happy 13th birthday to the twins that first made me a dad.  Ben and Nate, I love you both to the moon.

Saturday morning garden work reminds me of growing up.  The absolute best memories of working with my grandma picking all the fresh vegetables we would eat that night.  Hope your weekend is incredible!

BIG NEWS!! 📣

We can finally spill the beans on what we’ve been up to for the past four months… we have been busy filming SEASON FIVE of Fixer to Fabulous!!!! 16 new episodes will begin airing on @hgtv next January! 🙌

We couldn’t have ever seen this wild ride on the horizon but, gracious, are we thankful for it. We don’t take any of this for granted - the fact that we get to do what we love, alongside a team of people we adore is an absolute gift. And, the fact that you all choose to watch the journey from your living rooms with your families is just something we’ll never fully wrap our head around. We are truly, truly grateful!!!! THANK YOU and we will see you in January!! 😭🤍

#fixertofabulous

The smoke from the wildfires raging in Canada is not only affecting outside air quality, but now it is starting to affect indoor air quality as well. If you know anyone involved in the care of others, where air quality is becoming a problem, please send them this video and have them reach out online to: fixourair.com.  Daikin is sending out free, high-quality, brand new, air purifiers to help those in need.  Stay safe out there.
Happy birthday to my little man!  4 years old today!  Doesn’t matter if it’s in the yard, shop, house, garden, you name it; He’s ready to work and help.  I can’t imagine this life without Luke.
I know Father’s Day is just a couple days away and you may be looking for that last minute gift. Just today we got in my new favorite T-shirt. Check it out at @marrsmercantile

You know the great thing about a dad?  They stand beside you, even when there’s a lot of places they’d rather be.  Love you Dad!  Happy Fathers Day!  Promise I won’t get kicked out of anymore games as my kids coach. 😬

It’s Berry Fest weekend!!! 🫐🎉

We know so many of you have traveled from out of town to visit our farm tomorrow and we hope you have a wonderful weekend here in Northwest Arkansas. 🫶

We thought it would be fun to kick off your visit with a meet and greet today!

@dave.marrs and I will be at @marrsmercantile today between 11-12 CST and would love for you to come by and say hello!! 

See you all soon! 🤍
We are at the airport! This begins the family adventure to continue work on our European show “Fixer to Fabulous, Italiano”. First stop, England!  Wish us luck. 🤪
It’s crazy busy, but London has not disappointed.
Have a wonderful and safe 4th of July!  Spend it with family.  Spend it with friends.  Spend it thanking a veteran for making the USA the best country on earth!

Today, we are in Bayeux, France.  This town is in the Normandy region of France.  Tomorrow, we head to Omaha and Utah beach.  This has been something I have wanted to experience my whole life.  To see the beauty of this town and think that just a few miles away, such a momentous turn in our world happened on D-Day and the the years after is so powerful.  The people of this town still honor the sacrifices of so many so long ago.  Can’t wait for tomorrow!

Today we toured the cemetery, beaches, and cliffs of Normandy.  To say it was powerful is an understatement.  The soldiers who stormed the beaches of Utah and Omaha.  The rangers who climbed and fell from the cliffs of Pointe du Hoc.  The paratroopers who jumped into a black sky not knowing where they would land.  They all did this for something greater than themselves.  You can feel the gravity of it in all of these sacred places.  I feel honored to be an American!  I am so proud of the sacrifices made by those before us.  If you have a chance to go to Normandy, please do.  @alliedvictorytours

I still can’t get over the sacrifice and loss of so many for our freedom.  How we honor those who gave all is incredible.  Every night at 5pm two flags are lowered over those brave men and women.  They are all buried at random; regardless of religion, race, rank or gender.  The only exception are the 49 pairs of brothers who are buried next to each other.

Last post for Normandy.  If nothing else gets you, this is it.  This is the “Rose Garden” in the cemetery containing names of the soldiers bodies that were never found.  Reading the names literally broke me.  I was weeping like a child.  This quote was written over the names of the lost: “Here are recorded the names of Americans who gave their lives in the service of their country, and who sleep in unknown graves. This is their memorial, the whole earth their sepulchre”. I cannot emphasize enough the importance of this trip.  To remember history and sacrifice.  To be thankful to those who gave all.  And to the countries that promise to always remember them.  Go see it.
Windy day up on top of the tower in Montepulciano. 😂😂. Sooo worth it!  I love afternoon walks in this hill town of Tuscany.  @montepulciano_city_tower

Italy!  We’ve seen so much and everyday I am still amazed!  Getting to the top of the peaks where Michelangelo got marble 500 years ago, and being able to pick out a new slab for our Italy project with my family was a memory I’ll never  forget!  Can’t wait till you all see the show next spring.

Well.  It took us 6 months but @jennymarrs finally found Italian Joe Looney.  Old school tape measure, overalls, glasses, and he loved Jenny.  He wasn’t quite as grumpy as our Joe though.  We miss you Joe
Saying goodbye to an amazing couple of days in Venice.  Italy did not disappoint, it never does!  We were able to work, vacation, and dream a little bit.  Now on to Belgium and the Netherlands!

Ok, so it’s a little wrinkled, but it’s been a month of wearing it across Europe and the “Sawdust is just Man Glitter” shirt is a huge success.  I get lots of laughs and comments everywhere I go.  And now, you don’t have to come to the Marrs Mercantile to get it.  Buy it online at our store @marrsmercantile.  Or you can go to the link in my profile.

It’s good to be home.  There is a ton to catch up on, but you still need to have fun working.  The whole family pitched in yesterday harvesting some honey!  It was a lot of work, but we did it together and reaped the benefits with homemade bread covered in our own honey last night for dinner.

First impressions can mean everything. That’s why when it comes to the exterior of a home, I choose Mastic Siding by @plygem. Mastic offers more for the home – more vinyl siding styles and colors, more accessories and companion products, and more performance-backed guarantees to reflect the personality of those who live there. Check out the link in my bio to learn more about our partnership, and why Jenny and I choose #Mastic for our home renovations.

Yesterday, @jennymarrs got the final copy of her book,  House + Love = Home,  and our family could not be more excited! She has put so much of her heart into every page.  This book is great!  I hope you check it out.  I promise you won’t be disappointed.  The release date is in November, but you can preorder now at the link in my bio!  Love you Jenny Marrs

Truly amazing morning of fishing with Donny @tailwaterclub.  I am constantly amazed at all of the natural resources and beauty we have here in Arkansas.  This incredible fly fishing is less than an hour from the house.  And, there is nothing better than a fresh, cold, river during such a hot summer.  Highly recommended!
Evening walks with the girls checking on the baby cows and training the grape vines is the best!

Family dinner, no matter where, is a treasured time. This summer has been full of travels with the kids. We had such a great time, and will forever treasure the memories we made. Now, it’s back to the grind and school.  Hope you all have a wonderful weekend, wherever you are!

So, most of you probably know this, but I just learned it this year.  I have NEVER been able to grow good tomatoes.  This year a friend told me to add epsom salt at the base of the plant because it probably needed magnesium.  I did, and I have picked more tomatoes than ever before.  This is what I get every two days!  We are now canning, making fresh red sauce for our pasta dinners,  and eating the freshest tomatoes every meal.
Mornings on the farm are the best!  Baby cows, grapes on the vine, green grass, and peace!  It’s a happy place to be for sure!

Fun day in Detroit with @bargainblock with @keithbynum_ and @emuralit and @jennymarrs.  Their craftsmanship is incredible.  Watch them tomorrow night on @hgtv for their season 3 premiere, and look for us on an episode of their show later this fall.
Working on a cool project for such a great episode coming up this January on @hgtv .  Any guesses?
“Nothing to see here!  No Dad,  I’m not destroying your foam board” 😂😂😂
Little man helping out!  He loves the garden

The boys and I went to get our annual haircut refresh before school started a few days ago.  I can’t believe they are already in 8th grade.  It’s flying by, so I’m definitely trying to hold on to any traditions I can.  This is a great one where just the three of us head to dinner and @thegentsplace_bentonville to get an amazing haircut and a little time to hang out together.  I highly recommend it, you should definitely check it out.
Working on a fun ceiling!  Can’t wait to show you the finished product!

Got to spend a few days away with the family, and guess what?  @jennymarrs convinced us (made us)😬😂 get a new family picture!  So glad she did.  Hope you all had a wonderful weekend and got to spend it with loved ones!!!!

It has felt especially significant to place a flag on our completed renovations this week. 🇺🇸

#neverforget

Starting the day off in my favorite t-shirt. Today is demo day for our crew and this shirt will for sure have sawdust on it by the end of the day. Buy it now at @marrsmercantile or in the link in my profile.

Tough day for filming! 😂😂😂. If someone’s got to sleep though, it might as well be our sound guy Grant.  On a more serious note, I’m thinking about the chair becoming a permanent fixture in my driveway.  What are the rules about recliners in front yards outside anyway?  I’m pretty sure @jennymarrs and I would have drastically differing views!
Still picking tomatoes.  Anyone need any?😬😬.

Dave brought all of his own tools this trip because we have a ton of work to get finished (surprisingly, the hand chisel to build furniture in a day just didn’t cut it last time 😆). We are both SO happy to be back at @camposasso for another check-in on the renovation for our friends here. 

Fixer to Fabulous: Italiano is coming this spring!! 

#fixertofabulousitaliano 🇮🇹

A huge thank you to @sweetfreedomcheese, @bikerackbrewingco and everyone who joined us last night! It was a great evening together learning about cheese and beer, as well as woodworking with @dave.marrs!

Photos | @mike_davello

@jennymarrs and I had the privilege to be a part of a six part digital series called The Sustainability Series.  This series focuses on sustainability without sacrifice. What does that mean?  We aren’t  asking you to give up comforts and go live in the woods.  Rather, Technology is answering many of the problems we are facing with the rising prices in energy and @daikincomfort is leading the way with that technology.  Right now, in this crazy world of inflation, we will give you simple but effective practices that will not only help the environment, but will help your wallet as well.  I hope you can check it out tonight on HGtV at 9:39 pm and then check out my link in bio for the website and future episodes #ad
This horse.  I have to say, she’s starting to grow on me.

It’s time for the 2nd Annual Gentsgiving! Join us November 9th as we enjoy an incredible lineup of bourbons while also giving back to 2 charities, @sofwarriorfnd and @pancan. Plus, it’s at the Berry Farm! You wouldn’t want to miss this. See the link in bio for tickets.
Getting to hang out with these two lovely ladies for a couple days work in San Diego!  What a beautiful city

We can finally share the news … we have an airdate for Season 5 of Fixer to Fabulous! Sixteen brand new episodes will begin airing on Tuesday, November 7, at 8|7c on @hgtv 🎉!

We’ve been working all year on these renovations and can’t wait to share them with you all. This season, we renovate a home for dear friends, a wedding takes place on the show and we tackle our most personal renovation to date! We’ll share new animals, new families, and a lot of laughter. 

Our prayer for this season continues to be that our show is a light in this dark world. The privilege of being invited into your living room each week is not one we take lightly and we sincerely hope you walk away each Tuesday inspired and encouraged to make your home a beautiful reflection of you and your family. 🤍

See you in THREE weeks!!! 🎬📺

Photo credit: @mike_davello
If you’re gonna build some trusses, might as well include the whole family.  I love this kid’s willingness to help
What a beautiful day to spend in our nations capital!  Family, sun, and amazing fall weather.  I’m feeling pretty blessed right now

It has all of the features you would expect in traditional vinyl siding, plus enhanced technology that helps to keep vibrant colors even against extreme hot weather, cold weather, and sun exposure.  It also requires little to no maintenance – saving homeowners time and money. If you’re thinking about installing vinyl siding on your home, check out Mastic Siding by @plygem. I’m also putting a link in my bio for tips to help select the perfect siding for your home.
I got a little break while Jenny was filming yesterday.  Perfect chance to hang with the puppies!
Fall, fires, cold weather.  I’m in my happy place!  Anyone else with me?

We adore @keithbynum_ and @emuralit (and @shea.whitfield!) and immediately said YES when they asked us to help them out on a renovation in Detroit. They were working on an Italian-inspired home and we loved being a small part of this one! We had the best time visiting our friends and doing our part to repay them for the way they’ve helped us out in the past (the mural at @marrsmercantile 🙌). 

Tune in to the season finale of Bargain Block tonight at 9/8c on @hgtv to see the four of us at work! 🇮🇹♥️

Drinking water safe, lightweight and made in the USA!  If you need to buy a hose, the Flexon FeatherLite Hose does it all.  Our family uses this hose all year long, whether it’s washing the dogs, filling water troughs, or just getting a drink. Check it out at the link in my bio. #flexonhose

Over this past week, I have been building a bourbon display cabinet for the 2nd Annual Gentsgiving that we are hosting at the Berry Farm. I used an old door from The Welcome Inn and added led backlit lights.  Perfect to display all the amazing bourbon you own and hopefully find at the event.  Come check it out on November 9th while enjoying an incredible lineup of bourbon.  All proceeds benefit the @pancan and @sofwarriorfnd. See the link in bio to get your tickets.
Season 5 premiere is tonight!!!!!! Ok @hgtv at 8/7 c.  Don’t miss it!

Today, on Veterans Day, I want to take a moment and thank all of those individuals who have served, or are currently serving our country. 
  @jennymarrs and I got the opportunity to renovate a house this season on Fixer to Fabulous for one of those heroes. 
  Phillip and Jodi are a military family, and just a few weeks after we started, Phillip found out he was being deployed on his fourth tour serving our country.
